    • hashCode

      public int hashCode()
      The hashCode function is used to generate a unique hash code for each object. This is useful when storing objects in data structures such as HashMaps, where the hash code can be used to determine which bucket an object should be stored in. The default implementation of this function returns the memory address of the object, but it's often better to override this method and provide a more meaningful implementation.
